End of the trilogy and our three wanderers reach the end of their adventure, to meet their destinies at Montroy the Beautiful.
Theres the gorgeous Mariotte, intrigue, the gorgeous Mariotte, werewolves, burning at the stake, the gorgeous Mariotte, a mysterious rider from another time and, of course, the gorgeous Mariotte.
Lots of symbolism that doesnt spoil the read, beautiful art, flashbacks to books 1 &amp; 2, the attention to detail that Bourgeon is renowned for, rowdy prowling students who put damsels into distress, romance, human nature on trial, etc.
A bit lengthy at 144 pages but its needed to flesh out the story ...
